This infographic focuses on some of the key concepts of Digital Literacy Essentials in an eye-catching manner. In this image, digital literacy is defined as “the ability to use technology in an effective way, being ‘savvy’ in terms of digital platforms, and safe online practices." Some of the tools which are helpful for students are shown, such as Google Docs/Forms, GitHub, emails, and online learning sites. These are shown in an important manner. It also shows some safe online practices such as creating strong passwords, avoiding unknown links, safe data sharing, and enabling 2FA.

This infographic is created using Canva.
